# cleanup-checklist.example
# Final cleanup checklist before committing the completed guide.
# Check off each item manually after completing the step.
# Run ./cleanup-instructions.sh for detailed commands for each step.

## Pre-Commit Checks

[ ] Unstaged accidental files
    Command: git reset HEAD .
    Then re-add only intended files.

[ ] Removed test diagrams from diagrams/
    Delete any scratch files: test-*.mmd, test-*.svg, test-*.png
    Keep only final, named diagram files.

[ ] .claude/settings.local.json added to .gitignore
    Command: echo '.claude/settings.local.json' >> .gitignore
    Verify: git check-ignore -v .claude/settings.local.json

[ ] git status is clean
    Command: git status && git diff --staged
    No secrets, large binaries, or unintended files staged.

[ ] No hardcoded secrets in any committed file
    Check: grep -r "api_key\|password\|token\|secret" --include="*.json" --include="*.sh" .

## Validation Checks

[ ] All .mmd files have corresponding .svg outputs
    Command: ./run-validation.sh

[ ] All .vl.json files have corresponding .svg outputs
    Command: ./run-validation.sh

[ ] All .d2 files have corresponding .svg outputs
    Command: ./run-validation.sh

[ ] render-all-diagrams runs without errors on the diagrams/ directory
    Command: render-all-diagrams ./diagrams

## Infrastructure Verification (outside repo)

[ ] ~/bin/mermaid-render exists and is executable
    Command: which mermaid-render

[ ] ~/bin/vegalite-render exists and is executable
    Command: which vegalite-render

[ ] ~/bin/d2-render exists and is executable
    Command: which d2-render

[ ] ~/bin/render-all-diagrams exists and is executable
    Command: which render-all-diagrams

[ ] mermaid-diagrams skill is active in ~/.claude/settings.json
    Command: cat ~/.claude/settings.json | grep mermaid

[ ] PostToolUse hook is active for auto-rendering
    Command: cat ~/.claude/settings.json | grep PostToolUse

## Final Commit

[ ] Commit message follows conventional format
    Example: feat: complete Mermaid hybrid stack guide (Phases 0-13)

[ ] All phase directories are included in the commit
    Verify: git diff --staged --name-only | grep phase-

[ ] Project README documents the infrastructure setup steps
    Future collaborators need to know to run install scripts.
